<scriptment id="24000" point="garriot" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-06-22" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>Yuki hears something over the radio.</narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="radio" voicelang="ja">...game designer and space-tourist,</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="radio" voicelang="ja">has announced that he will put all effort into advancing space tourism,</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="radio" voicelang="ja">using funds from the liquidation of his company, Destination Games.</line>
		<narration>The radio cuts to an interview. The space-tourist's voice starts in English and leads to its Japanese translation.</narration>
		<line id="4000" speaker="garriott" voicelang="ja">...even my greatest ideas are no match for the final frontier.</line>
		<line id="5000" speaker="garriott" voicelang="ja">I mean, this is the universe we're dealing with, here.</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="garriott" voicelang="ja">I just think it's time to quit video games and move on.</line>
	</part>
</scriptment>